<#GAPDoc Label="IsFreeCongruence">
  <ManSection>
    <Filt Name = "IsFreeCongruence" Arg = "obj" Type = "Category"/>
    <Returns><K>true</K> or <K>false</K>.</Returns>
    <Description>
      This category contains any congruence over a free semigroup or free
      monoid.  It can be used in the same way as any other semigroup congruence.
      See <Ref Prop = "IsSemigroupCongruence"/>. <P/>

      <Example><![CDATA[
gap> F := FreeSemigroup(1);;
gap> x := GeneratorsOfSemigroup(F)[1];;
gap> pairs := [[x ^ 2, x ^ 4]];;
gap> cong := SemigroupCongruence(F, pairs);
<semigroup congruence over <free semigroup on the generators 
[ s1 ]> with 1 generating pairs>
gap> IsFreeCongruence(cong);
true
gap> NrEquivalenceClasses(cong);
3
]]></Example>
    </Description>
  </ManSection>
<#/GAPDoc>
